This paper focuses on the application of hyper-heuristic algorithms for test case generation in industrial software, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of reinforcement learning and Q-learning mechanism also suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which can be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
